The article discusses the efforts made by the United States to promote food security in Africa. President Obama has made food security a foreign policy priority, and the US has launched initiatives such as Feed the Future and the New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition. These initiatives aim to invest in countries' national food security plans, promote agricultural research and innovation, and build capacity. The article highlights the progress made so far, including private sector investments, job creation, and policy reforms in African countries. The US is also committed to training young people, supporting data initiatives, and investing in agricultural insurance. Additionally, the US has played a central role in the foundation of the global Alliance for Climate Smart Agriculture. Overall, the US is taking a whole-of-government approach, with various agencies working together to support food security in Africa.